---
import Layout from '@/components/layout/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Chatbot Example">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">Chatbot Example</h1>
    
    <div class="prose max-w-none mb-8">
      <p>
        This page demonstrates how to use the recruiter chatbot component. The chatbot is designed to help recruiters
        interact with your portfolio website and learn more about your skills, experience, and projects.
      </p>
      
      <h2>Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Real-time chat interface</li>
        <li>Authentication with Supabase</li>
        <li>Conversation history storage</li>
        <li>OpenAI integration for natural language processing</li>
        <li>Responsive design for mobile and desktop</li>
      </ul>
      
      <h2>How to Use</h2>
      <p>
        Click the chat button in the bottom-right corner to open the chatbot. You can ask questions about my
        experience, skills, projects, or anything else you'd like to know about me as a candidate.
      </p>
      
      <h2>Implementation</h2>
      <p>
        The chatbot is implemented using React components within an Astro website. It uses Supabase for authentication
        and data storage, and OpenAI for natural language processing.
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded-md">
        <p class="font-mono text-sm">
          // Import the components<br />
          import &#123; ChatbotProvider &#125; from '@/components/chatbot/ChatbotProvider';<br />
          import &#123; ChatWidget &#125; from '@/components/chatbot/ui/ChatWidget';<br />
          <br />
          // Basic usage<br />
          &lt;ChatbotProvider&gt;<br />
          &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ChatWidget /&gt;<br />
          &lt;/ChatbotProvider&gt;<br />
          <br />
          // With controlled state (React component example)<br />
          // const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);<br />
          // <br />
          // &lt;ChatbotProvider&gt;<br />
          // &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;ChatWidget <br />
          // &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;isOpen=&#123;isOpen&#125; <br />
          // &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;onOpenChange=&#123;setIsOpen&#125; <br />
          // &nbsp;&nbsp;/&gt;<br />
          // &lt;/ChatbotProvider&gt;
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="bg-yellow-100 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 text-yellow-700 p-4 my-4">
        <p class="font-bold">Note:</p>
        <p>The actual chatbot component is temporarily disabled on this page. The chatbot will be available once all the backend services are properly configured.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout> 